content: Season of television series The fifth season of *[Supermodel Me](/wiki/Supermodel_Me)* or *(Supermodel Me: Sirens)* aired in 2014, with the shooting location being moved from [Hong Kong](/wiki/Hong_Kong) to [Malaysia](/wiki/Malaysia). The judging panel this season include [Lisa Selesner](/wiki/Lisa_Selesner), Ase Wang and Dom Lau. This fifth season have aired, launches on [Diva (Asian TV channel)](/wiki/Diva_(Asian_TV_channel)) and [Azio TV](/wiki/Azio_TV). This season 5 was also take place in [Kuala Lumpur](/wiki/Kuala_Lumpur), [Malaysia](/wiki/Malaysia) for the very first time in [Supermodel Me](/wiki/Supermodel_Me) show history. This season will feature 12 contestants; two each from [Japan](/wiki/Japan), the [Philippines](/wiki/Philippines), [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore), [South Korea](/wiki/South_Korea) and [Thailand](/wiki/Thailand), one each from [Indonesia](/wiki/Indonesia) and [Malaysia](/wiki/Malaysia). The prizes for this cycle were a modelling contract with Premier Model Management in [London](/wiki/London) and a cash prize of S$35.000.
